(22, 1, '2014-08-07 20:17:29', '2014-08-07 20:17:29', '<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Debbie-Whipple.png" alt="Debbie Whipple" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Debbie Whipple</h2>\r\n<h4>General Manager</h4>\r\nDebbie holds the General Manager position at McDowell Village. She began her career at McDowell Village in the sales and marketing department when the community opened in January of 2006. In 2007 she was promoted to General Manager. Debbie left McDowell Village briefly in 2011 to pursue another opportunity within the market. We were fortunate to welcome her back to our community in October of 2012.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining McDowell Village Debbie worked in the marketing and finance fields. She is married, has one daughter, and is very involved in her community. She currently holds the position of President of Freedom Academy School Board of Directors. Debbie has an undergraduate degree in Broadcasting from the University of Oklahoma.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Michael-Bergmans.png" alt="Michael Bergmans" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Michael Bergmans</h2>\r\n<h4>Assistant General Manager</h4>\r\nMichael started his career as a chef and spent over 18 years in some of Arizona''s top restaurants and catering companies. He toured the country as a private chef for some celebrities including; Bette Midler, Ricky Martin, Tina Turner, NSYNC, Cher and Janet Jackson. Michael has taken his love for people and commitment to customer service to the next level as Assistant General Manager. For the past 3 years Michael has enjoyed working with management and the residents to make McDowell Village one of the top Senior Residents in the area. He has used his experience in the food industry to keep the McDowell Village Restaurant fresh and inviting.\r\n\r\n"I am thrilled to be a part of the team at McDowell Village and I am excited to extend an invite to come and dine in our restaurant. While you''re here, take a tour of the entire resort-like community! You will soon discover the McDowell Village is where you belong."\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Chef-Thomas-Miranda.png" alt="Thomas Miranda" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Thomas Miranda</h2>\r\n<h4>Chef</h4>\r\nThomas has been in the food and beverage industry for 13 years, he has a real passion for food and loves to cook. His prior restaurant position before joining the team at McDowell Village was at a similar senior living community in North Phoenix. "My favorite meal to cook is BBQ Ribs, baked beans and cream corn…mmm”. I am proud to be the Executive Chef of McDowell Village and hope to take food and service to another level. My hobbies include playing basketball and spending time with my son Josh."\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Jay-Beaird.png" alt="Jay Beaird" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Jay Beaird</h2>\r\n<h4>Marketing Director</h4>\r\nJay has been with McDowell Village since August 2008. Prior to joining McDowell Village Jay had a very successful career in the toy and hobby industry. He was a manufactures representative for over 30 companies and his previous position before joining McDowell was as the Western Regional Sales Manager for the world’s largest model railroad company. Jay is married with six children and two grandchildren.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Kristin-Koga-London.png" alt="Kristin Koga-London" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Kristin Koga-London</h2>\r\n<h4>Marketing Manager</h4>\r\nKristin has been with McDowell Village since June 2010. Prior to joining McDowell Village Kristin was a regional sales director and has had a long, successful sales and marketing career. Kristin has a dual degree in Business Management and Marketing. She is married and is the mother of two boys.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Pam-Clark.png" alt="Pam Clark" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Pam Clark</h2>\r\n<h4>Business Office Manager</h4>\r\nPam has worked at McDowell Village since 2006 and was the Front Desk Supervisor before becoming the Business Office Manager. She was born and raised in North Dakota and has lived in Arizona since 1983. Pam acquired her customer service and bookkeeping skills while helping her husband run a small business for over 20 years. They have two daughters. "This job is never boring. There is always something interesting happening."\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Chris-Okeke.png" alt="Chris Okeke" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Chris Okeke</h2>\r\n<h4>Fitness Instructor</h4>\r\nChris is the Fitness Instructor at McDowell Village. He has a passion for working with seniors, having grown up spending a lot of time with his own grandparents. He gained experience working in outpatient/inpatient physical therapy clinics. Chris earned his Bachelor of Science degree in Exercise &amp; Fitness Management from the University of Central Oklahoma. He is married and has two dogs.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Teri-Azlin.png" alt="Teri Azlin" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Teri Azlin</h2>\r\n<h4>Activities Director</h4>\r\nTeri has been with McDowell Village since May of 2008. Although her current position is a new field for her, she has been in the "people" business her entire career. Teri''s degree is in the field of Architecture, an industry she worked in for several years. After having children Teri switched careers to work as an administrative assistant and helped run an office with 100+ employees, which gave her a flexible schedule before moving to McDowell Village. She is married and has two children.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Ilona-Herbelin.png" alt="Ilona Herbelin" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Ilona Herbelin</h2>\r\n<h4>Resident Services Director</h4>\r\nIlona is the Resident Service Director for Assisted Living at McDowell. She was present for the foundation and development of the Assisted Living services in 2010. She is a Registered Nurse with a background in cardiology, acute care, geriatrics and business management. Ilona is passionate about her work and advocacy for our residents.\r\n\r\nIlona is married and has two small children. She is an avid animal lover, and dog owner. Ilona is originally from Oregon and returns to visit the coast any chance she can get. During her time off she enjoys photography, travel, antiquing, real estate, off-roading and swimming with her children.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Meet Our Team', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'meet-our-team', '', '', '2014-11-25 23:42:27', '2014-11-25 23:42:27', '', 12, 'http://new.westliving.net/?page_id=22', 2, 'page', '', 0),
(496, 7, '2014-10-03 00:44:53', '2014-10-03 00:44:53', '<div class="media">\r\n<div class="pull-left"></div>\r\n<div class="media-body">\r\n<h2 class="media-heading">Sam Faye</h2>\r\n<h4>General Manager</h4>\r\nSam is a heck of a guy.  Personable and friendly...he''s always there to help.  A great sense of humor and he''s quick to make you laugh.  Don''t let his Bostonian background fool you, he won''t steal your wallet or push you around.  Well, he may push you around if you are in a wheel chair.  But seriously, he''s the real deal.  And a dealer he is!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="media">\r\n<div class="pull-left"></div>\r\n<div class="media-body">\r\n<h2 class="media-heading">Carrie Compton</h2>\r\n<h4>Sales Director</h4>\r\n..another keeper.  Industry and local professional...a closer...\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="media">\r\n<div class="media-body">\r\n<h2 class="media-heading">Stephen Pratt</h2>\r\n<h4>Marketing Director</h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="media">\r\n<div class="pull-left"></div>\r\n<div class="media-body">\r\n<h2 class="media-heading">Allen Johnson</h2>\r\n<h4>Food &amp; Beverage Director</h4>\r\n<span style="color: #000000; font-family: Calibri;">Allen Johnson, Chef AJ, is a San Antonio, Texas native. He attended The Culinary Institute of America in Hyde Park, New York obtaining a degree in Culinary Arts. He also focused on French Pastries at Ecole Superieure Cuisine de Francaise Ferrandi in Paris, France. Chef AJ has opened more than 20 restaurants domestically and internationally, but his most memorable experiences have taken him to the 1996 Olympic Games in Atlanta, The Wine Spectator Restaurant in Napa Valley, and cooking for more than 6,000 Marines and Army in Kuwait. He also ranked third in the Top 10 breakfast spots at Lockwood in Paris, France 2013 by Thrillst, and was commended for his cuisine in Travel and Leisure. He enjoys sourcing seasonal products, cooking from scratch, and creating an environment his staff and guests will enjoy. He recently moved to Riverside, CA with his wife and enjoys skydiving and motorcycling on his time off. He looks forward to working with the team and residents at Estancia Del Sol as Food and Beverage Director.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Meet Our Team', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-10-03 00:44:53', '2014-10-03 00:44:53', '', 22, 'http://www.estanciads.com/redesign/22-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(356, 2, '2014-09-11 17:15:58', '2014-09-11 17:15:58', '<div class="media">\r\n  <div class="pull-left">\r\n    <img class="media-object" src="/redesign/wp-content/uploads/gerry-vadnais.jpg" alt="Gerry Vadnais"/>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="media-body">\r\n    <h2 class="media-heading">Gerry Vadnais</h2>\r\n    <h4>General Manager</h4>\r\n    <p>Gerry Vadnais is the General Manager for the Commons at Elk Grove. Originally from Rhode Island, Gerry left after graduating from college. Gerry started in the hotel industry with Hyatt Hotels while living in Chicago. His work gave him the opportunity to live in varied locations such as Boston, Beverly Hills, Maui and Vail, Colorado. In 2007 he transitioned his hospitality skills from hotels to Senior Living. During the past six years Gerry has served as the Executive Director of Communities offering Independent and Assisted Living, Memory Care and most recently a Continuing Care Retirement Community in Palo Alto. Gerry currently resides in the East Bay.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="media">\r\n  <div class="pull-left">\r\n    <img class="media-object" src="/redesign/wp-content/uploads/lisa-bailey.jpg" alt="Lisa Bailey"/>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="media-body">\r\n    <h2 class="media-heading">Lisa Bailey</h2>\r\n    <h4>Business Office Manager</h4>\r\n    <p>Lisa is the Business Office Manager for The Commons at Elk Grove. She joined the Team in August 2009, with over 16 years’ experience of mainstream banking, along with organizational and customer orientation skills. “I am suited very well with a balance of running the Business, aligned with the needs and wishes of the residents as my daily goal.” says Lisa. She volunteers and is active in the community of Elk Grove with fund raising for localized charities. She is married with three children and two grandchildren.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="media">\r\n  <div class="pull-left">\r\n    <img class="media-object" src="/redesign/wp-content/uploads/tammy-schwartz.jpg" alt="Tammy Cahill"/>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="media-body">\r\n    <h2 class="media-heading">Tammy Cahill</h2>\r\n    <h4>Community Relations Director</h4>\r\n    <p>Tammy is the Community Relations Director for The Commons at Elk Grove. She received her marketing and sales experience while working in the banking industry. After spending quality time volunteering at a senior center in Loomis she realized her passion of working with mature adults and their families. She lives in Elk Grove with her husband, and longtime resident of Elk Grove, Tom Cahill. Tammy is the mother of two children Jason and Kristy and three grandchildren Weston, Rylan and Ruby.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="media">\r\n  <div class="pull-left">\r\n    <img class="media-object" src="/redesign/wp-content/uploads/matthew-minch.jpg" alt="Matthew Minch"/>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="media-body">\r\n    <h2 class="media-heading">Matthew Minch</h2>\r\n    <h4>Maintenance Director</h4>\r\n    <p>Matthew manages both the Housekeeping and Maintenance departments at The Commons at Elk Grove. Before joining the Team, Matthew worked over four years in the hotel industry with Hilton and Holiday Inn, where he expanded on his skills as maintenance operative. Matthew earned his A.S. at San Joaquin Valley College. He also studied Mechanical Engineering as well as Computer Aid Drafting at Delta College. Matthew has had some of the best experiences of his career working with seniors, he especially enjoys hearing all their amazing life stories. Matthew currently resides in Sacramento along with his wife and their two cats.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>', 'Meet Our Team', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-11 17:15:58', '2014-09-11 17:15:58', '', 22, 'http://www.estanciads.com/redesign/22-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
