(91, 1, '2014-08-08 18:14:17', '2014-08-08 18:14:17', '<p>Gary and Mary West are successful entrepreneurs and pioneering philanthropists working together through their Foundation with a commitment to making a significant positive impact for the greater good. Their purposeful philanthropic investments include these initiative areas:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\r\n    <li>To significantly improve the lives of low-income seniors in San Diego and Omaha by supporting programs that address their needs.&nbsp; Enabling older adults to age independently and maintain health and wellness for as long as possible. In addition, the Foundation supports research efforts and validation processes through Infrastructure IndependentTM resources enabling seniors to better manage chronic disease and prevent unwanted hospitalizations.</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>To change the pattern of chronic unemployment in our urban neighborhoods by helping disadvantaged young people secure jobs with career advancement opportunity.</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>To support the training and deployment of service canines to people in need, especially seniors and disabled veterans of the Armed Forces of the United States.</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>To lower the cost of healthcare by encouraging innovative, patient-centered solutions by supporting medical and scientific research development, policy studies, education and advocacy.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Gary &amp; Mary pioneered West Corporation in 1986, a world recognized leader of technology-driven communications with more than 35,000 employees.&nbsp; West Corporation was sold to a consortium of private equity firms in 2006, enabling Gary &amp; Mary to pursue their purposeful philanthropic endeavors. Multiple business and non-profit entities resulted in the creation of: West Development, a hospitality operating company; <a href="http://www.garyandmarywestfoundation.org/" target="_blank">The Gary &amp; Mary West Foundation</a>, a philanthropic wireless health, caring for seniors and education entity; and West Partners, a private equity and real estate investment firm. WESTliving, a portfolio company of West Partners, was formed in 2009 to develop, acquire and manage senior housing communities, expanding Gary &amp; Mary’s long-term vision to support older adults.</p>', 'About Gary &amp; Mary West', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '24-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-08-08 18:14:17', '2014-08-08 18:14:17', '', 24, 'http://new.westliving.net/24-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(92, 1, '2014-08-08 18:16:11', '2014-08-08 18:16:11', '<p class="intro-text">Gary and Mary West are successful entrepreneurs and pioneering philanthropists working together through their Foundation with a commitment to making a significant positive impact for the greater good. Their purposeful philanthropic investments include these initiative areas:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\r\n    <li>To significantly improve the lives of low-income seniors in San Diego and Omaha by supporting programs that address their needs.&nbsp; Enabling older adults to age independently and maintain health and wellness for as long as possible. In addition, the Foundation supports research efforts and validation processes through Infrastructure IndependentTM resources enabling seniors to better manage chronic disease and prevent unwanted hospitalizations.</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>To change the pattern of chronic unemployment in our urban neighborhoods by helping disadvantaged young people secure jobs with career advancement opportunity.</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>To support the training and deployment of service canines to people in need, especially seniors and disabled veterans of the Armed Forces of the United States.</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>To lower the cost of healthcare by encouraging innovative, patient-centered solutions by supporting medical and scientific research development, policy studies, education and advocacy.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Gary &amp; Mary pioneered West Corporation in 1986, a world recognized leader of technology-driven communications with more than 35,000 employees.&nbsp; West Corporation was sold to a consortium of private equity firms in 2006, enabling Gary &amp; Mary to pursue their purposeful philanthropic endeavors. Multiple business and non-profit entities resulted in the creation of: West Development, a hospitality operating company; <a href="http://www.garyandmarywestfoundation.org/" target="_blank">The Gary &amp; Mary West Foundation</a>, a philanthropic wireless health, caring for seniors and education entity; and West Partners, a private equity and real estate investment firm. WESTliving, a portfolio company of West Partners, was formed in 2009 to develop, acquire and manage senior housing communities, expanding Gary &amp; Mary’s long-term vision to support older adults.</p>', 'About Gary &amp; Mary West', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '24-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-08-08 18:16:11', '2014-08-08 18:16:11', '', 24, 'http://new.westliving.net/24-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(93, 1, '2014-08-08 18:17:04', '2014-08-08 18:17:04', '<h3>Senior Living with one goal in mind: to create a sense of belonging for seniors and their families.</h3>\r\n<p>Formed in early 2009, WESTliving offers a true sense of belonging for seniors and their families. It''s a feeling that begins the moment you''re invited to "make yourself at home," and continues through every thoughtful, personal detail. Because not only do we understand the importance of world-class customer service, we thrive on it. That''s why every Team Member is empowered and trained to anticipate needs and create solutions on the spot with one goal in mind: to surprise and delight every day. By combining our signature WESTclass service with comfortable, elegant surroundings, we''ve created a welcoming environment filled with empathy and respect.</p>', 'Welcome To Senior Living, WESTliving Style.', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-08-08 18:17:04', '2014-08-08 18:17:04', '', 2, 'http://new.westliving.net/2-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(94, 1, '2014-08-08 18:19:07', '2014-08-08 18:19:07', '<p class="intro-text">At WESTliving our mission centers on delivering exceptional services and experiences by inspiring and empowering our Team Members to make a meaningful difference in the lives of those we serve.  WESTliving’s culture is grounded in the fact that these daily actions and behaviors support our shared vision to be the most respected and recognized service company in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>WESTliving was formed in early 2009 to own and operate hospitality based senior living communities providing exceptional variety of lifestyles, wellness, and care options. WESTclass uncompromising quality is apparent with respect to building standards, amenities, Team Member’s commitment, as well as the integration of innovative programs and wellness options designed to accommodate and support an array of lifestyles and needs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The WESTclass Team of talented and experienced leaders in the industry bring a customer centered approach to senior living. Team members are driven by WESTliving Core Values, Mission, and Service Standards as guiding principles to be engaged, responsible and attentive to all we serve in achieving our Vision.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>WESTliving is located in Carlsbad, California and operates within the Pacific and Southwest regions of the United States. Maintaining a boutique and uniquely focused approached as a regional operator enables WESTliving to stay true to its vision of service excellence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At WESTliving, we make it easy for residents to remain a part of the larger community just outside their door. This is why we reach out into the neighborhood to support and partner with cultural centers, schools and senior advocacy groups, to name a few. You will find intergenerational experiences, philanthropy and good ol’ neighborliness alive and well. This is what we call a true sense of belonging.</p>', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '12-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-08-08 18:19:07', '2014-08-08 18:19:07', '', 12, 'http://new.westliving.net/12-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(95, 1, '2014-08-08 18:22:50', '2014-08-08 18:22:50', '<p class="intro-text">Senior living communities with a difference: a true sense of belonging.</p>\r\n<h3>ARIZONA</h3>\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.mcdowellvillage.com/" target="_blank">McDowell Village</a></h4>\r\n<p>McDowell Village is a 207 unit independent and assisted living community located in South Scottsdale - &frac14; mile west of highway 101 and 2 miles east of highway 202, which provides access to downtown Phoenix. The Community benefits from the City of Scottsdale sponsored 38,000 square foot Granite Reef Senior Center, which provides educational, recreational and social activities.&nbsp;<a href="http://www.mcdowellvillage.com/" target="_blank">MORE &gt;&gt;</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>CALIFORNIA</h3>\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.commonsatelkgrove.com/" target="_blank">The Commons at Elk Grove</a></h4>\r\n<p>The Commons at Elk Grove is a 95 unit independent, assisted living and memory care community conveniently located in the heart of Elk Grove. Residents enjoy private, spacious studios, one-and two-bedroom suites surrounded by their own furniture and personal treasures. Residents have a place to call their own. Cozy yet elegant surroundings, stimulating activities and excursions, exceptional amenities and extra help when needed-you''ll find all this and more at The Commons at Elk Grove Assisted Living Community. <a href="http://www.commonsatelkgrove.com/" target="_blank">MORE &gt;&gt;</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.commonsonthornton.com" target="_blank">The Commons on Thornton</a></h4>\r\n<p>The Commons on Thornton is a 100 unit independent, assisted living and memory care community conveniently located in the heart of the Central Valley. Residents enjoy private, spacious studios, one-and two-bedroom suites surrounded by their own furniture and personal treasures. Residents have a place to call their own. Cozy yet elegant surroundings, stimulating activities and excursions, exceptional amenities and extra help when needed-you''ll find all this and more at The Commons&nbsp;on Thornton&nbsp;Assisted Living Community. <a href="http://www.commonsonthornton.com" target="_blank">MORE &gt;&gt;</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.commonsatunionranch.com" target="_blank">The Commons at Union Ranch</a></h4>\r\n<p>The Commons at Union Ranch is a 98 unit independent, assisted living and memory care community conveniently located in the heart of the Central Valley. Residents enjoy private, spacious studios, one-and two-bedroom suites surrounded by their own furniture and personal treasures. Residents have a place to call their own. Cozy yet elegant surroundings, stimulating activities and excursions, exceptional amenities and extra help when needed-you''ll find all this and more at The Commons at Union Ranch Assisted Living Community. <a href="http://www.commonsatunionranch.com" target="_blank">MORE &gt;&gt;</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.dalecommons.com" target="_blank">Dale Commons</a></h4>\r\n<p>Dale Commons is a 98 unit independent and assisted living community located in the heart of Stanislaus County, Modesto. Residents enjoy private, spacious studios, one-and two-bedroom suites surrounded by their own furniture and personal treasures. Residents have a place to call their own. Cozy yet elegant surroundings, stimulating activities and excursions, exceptional amenities and extra help when needed-you''ll find all this and more at Dale Commons Assisted Living Community. <a href="http://www.dalecommons.com" target="_blank">MORE &gt;&gt;</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.estanciads.com">Estancia Del Sol</a></h4>\r\n<p>Estancia Del Sol is a 117 unit independent, assisted living and memory care community conveniently located in the heart of Corona, CA. Residents enjoy private, spacious studios, one-and two-bedroom suites surrounded by their own furniture and personal treasures. Residents have a place to call their own. Cozy yet elegant surroundings, stimulating activities and excursions, exceptional amenities and extra help when needed-you''ll find all this and more at Estancia Del Sol Assisted Living Community. <a href="http://www.estanciads.com">MORE &gt;&gt;</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.thereserveatthousandoaks.com" target="_blank">The Reserve at Thousand Oaks</a></h4>\r\n<p>The Reserve at Thousand Oaks is a 140 unit independent and assisted living community occupying a magnificent hilltop site in Thousand Oaks, affording breathtaking views of the entire Conejos Valley and the Santa Rosa foothills. The Ventura freeway is less than 10 minutes from your door and the Pacific Ocean is only 30 minutes to the south through the beautiful Santa Monica Mountains. <a href="http://www.thereserveatthousandoaks.com" target="_blank">MORE &gt;&gt;</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>WASHINGTON</h3>\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.thebellettini.com" target="_blank">The Bellettini</a></h4>\r\n<p>The Bellettini offers 145 senior apartment homes for those over the age of 62, featuring 25 different floor plans only steps away from the energy and buzz of downtown Bellevue, within the calm and comfort of residential living. One- and two-bedroom apartments range from 700 square feet to 2,400 square feet. Assisted living services can be added and customized at any time. <a href="http://www.thebellettini.com" target="_blank">MORE &gt;&gt;</a></p>', 'Locations', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '10-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-08-08 18:22:50', '2014-08-08 18:22:50', '', 10, 'http://new.westliving.net/10-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(96, 1, '2014-08-08 18:24:36', '2014-08-08 18:24:36', '<p class="intro-text">At WESTliving, creating a customer experience and anticipating needs through our WESTclass service is our hallmark. Anyone can say ‘make yourself at home.’ It is only when the warm and friendly environment meets genuine hospitality that brings those words to life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whatever your lifestyle living needs or wishes are, each day we strive to provide our customers with a WESTclass experience. “WESTclass” is our word that expresses a world-class standard in hospitality and services for older adults. The foundational values, the WESTliving mission and vision are what we build upon in careful selection of our Team Members to creating the WESTclass experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Our Values</h2>\r\n<h3>I.N.S.P.I.R.E.</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Integrity</strong> - We say what we do and do what we say – we are accountable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Neighborliness</strong> - We build lasting relationships in and around our communities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Service</strong> - We deliver WESTclass service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Profitability</strong> - We reinvest our financial success in our communities and our team members.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Innovation</strong> - We are forward-thinking and committed to continuous improvement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Respect</strong> - We value diversity and encourage individual thinking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Excellence</strong> - We focus on the details and provide a WESTclass experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Our Mission</h2>\r\n<p>With absolute devotion, WESTliving delivers exceptional service and experiences by inspiring and empowering our team members to make a meaningful difference in the lives of those we serve.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Our Vision</h2>\r\n<p>WESTliving will be the most respected and recognized service company in the world.</p>', 'Our Mission', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-08-08 18:24:36', '2014-08-08 18:24:36', '', 20, 'http://new.westliving.net/20-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
