(181, 1, '2014-07-02 17:00:02', '2014-07-02 17:00:02', '<h3>Location: Modesto, CA</h3>\r\n<h2>Position Summary:</h2>\r\n\r\nWe are seeking an individual with hospitality management experience to assume the role of Guest Services Manager. This person will be responsible for providing leadership and management to front desk and guest services team, as well as ensuring that the highest level of service is delivered to our customers.\r\n\r\nWESTliving is looking to fill this position with a person who possesses the following talents:\r\n\r\n<strong>Service</strong> – A drive to be of service to others.\r\n<strong>Ethics</strong> – A clear understanding of right and wrong which guides your actions.\r\n<strong>Arranger</strong> – An ability to orchestrate.\r\n<strong>Creativity</strong> - An ability to break existing configurations in favor of more effective/appealing ones.\r\n<strong>Individualized Perception</strong> – An awareness of and attentiveness to individual differences. \r\n\r\nIn addition to the talents listed above WESTliving is looking to fill this position with a person who possesses the following:\r\n\r\n<h3>Skills</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Communication</strong> – Able to instruct as well as listen. Effectively understands, deciphers and relates Westliving’s vision to employees.</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Leadership</strong> – Instills trust, provides direction, delegates’ responsibility and empowers others.</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Relationship Building</strong> – Builds personal and lasting professional relationships with customers and employees.</li>\r\n    <li>Proficient user of Microsoft Word and Outlook</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Knowledge</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>3-4 years of Hotel and/or Concierge style customer service experience</li>\r\n    <li>High School Diploma Required. A.A. preferred.</li>\r\n    <li>Understanding and experience with providing transportation service to multiple guests</li>\r\n    <li>Experience in implementing projects and policies</li>\r\n    <li>Experience in managing budgets and labor</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>About us</h3>\r\nWESTliving was formed in early 2009 to own and operate hospitality based senior living communities. Our communities provide a variety of lifestyles, wellness, and care options. We are uncompromising in our commitment to quality and service excellence. WESTliving’s culture is grounded in the fact that daily actions and behaviors support our shared vision to be the most respected and recognized service company in the world.\r\n\r\nThe WESTclass Team of talented and experienced leaders in the industry bring a customer centered approach to senior living. Team members are driven by WESTliving Core Values, Mission, and Service Standards as guiding principles to be engaged, responsible and attentive to all we serve in achieving our Vision.\r\n\r\n<h3>Join our Team!</h3>\r\nAs we look forward to future growth, we are committed to providing our employees with the tools they need to succeed, as well as providing a challenging work environment with opportunities to make meaningful contributions. Our benefits package includes: medical, dental, vision, life insurance, vacation, and a 401(k) plan with a generous employer match.', 'Guest Services Manager', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'guest-services-manager-dale-commons', '', '', '2014-08-29 16:04:20', '2014-08-29 16:04:20', '', 0, 'http://new.westliving.net/?post_type=careers&#038;p=181', 0, 'careers', '', 0),
