(620, 7, '2014-11-04 00:57:05', '2014-11-04 00:57:05', '<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/sam-faye.jpg" alt="Sam Faye" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Sam Faye</h2>\r\n<h4>General Manager</h4>\r\nAs our General Manager, Sam Faye brings senior housing hospitality leadership to a new level at Estancia Del Sol.  With over 20 years of diverse experience from both the senior housing and hospitality industries, Sam leads our team of service professionals.  Sam’s award-winning background includes pioneer work in establishing market awareness with successful openings of new senior housing communities in California.  His customer engagement, organizational skills, and attention to detail sets the bar high through a team approach to service delivery.  Sam developed his hospitality roots in many well-known lodging organizations, acting as the catalyst to apply his hospitality expertise to an older adult customer in early 2000.  He is a hands-on leader in supporting his team, while fostering operational plans for success.  Sam prides himself on building exceptional teams and delivering legendary service.  Couple this with his genuine sense of humor and quick wit to put anyone at ease, and we are confident you’ll experience memorable moments at Estancia Del Sol.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/carrie-compton.jpg" alt="Carrie Compton" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Carrie Compton</h2>\r\n<h4>Sales Director</h4>\r\nTwelve years ago, Carrie began her career in sales and marketing in the senior living industry. When asked what she loves most about this line of work she said, “Being able to make such a huge and meaningful difference in the lives of seniors and their families and to watch them smile, laugh and be loved by a caring staff. Moving to a Retirement Community for most seniors can be scary and a change they wish they didn’t have to make. But it gives me such pleasure to see how happy they become once they do make the move.”\r\n\r\nAfter 12 years and three communities later, Carrie is beyond happy and grateful to be given the position here at Estancia Del Sol. Being able to be a part of a flagship community for WESTliving is a dream come true.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/stephen-pratt.jpg" alt="Stephen Pratt" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Stephen Pratt</h2>\r\n<h4>Marketing Liaison</h4>\r\nStephen brings eight years of experience in Senior Housing to his position as Marketing Liaison. His journey in Senior Living began back in 2006. His multifaceted experience includes Server, Caregiver, Medication Tech, Concierge, Activities Coordinator, Administrative Assistant and Sales Counselor. Stephen states, “I became so attached to the residents after working in senior living for the last few years, it has become a passion — so much so that I don’t ever want to leave this industry!\r\n\r\nWork is not ‘work’ for me, because I get to do something I love doing and I’m able to share my life and accomplishments with, what seem like, adopted grandparents. It is a bond that is so hard to explain without being a part of it.” After graduating from California State University - Fullerton, Stephen began a position as a senior living Sales Counselor. One year later, WESTliving chose Stephen as their Marketing Liaison. “The best part about my job now is getting to hear the stories of each individual who walks through the door, and it is so gratifying being able to help people in their search for a better quality of life.”\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Meet Our Team', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-04 00:57:05', '2014-11-04 00:57:05', '', 22, 'http://www.estanciads.com/22-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
