(247, 2, '2014-09-04 17:13:22', '2014-09-04 17:13:22', '<p class="intro-text">At WESTliving, creating a customer experience and anticipating needs through our WESTclass service is our hallmark. Anyone can say ‘make yourself at home.’ It is only when the warm and friendly environment meets genuine hospitality that brings those words to life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whatever your lifestyle living needs or wishes are, each day we strive to provide our customers with a WESTclass experience. “WESTclass” is our word that expresses a world-class standard in hospitality and services for older adults. The foundational values, the WESTliving mission and vision are what we build upon in careful selection of our Team Members to creating the WESTclass experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Our Values</h2>\r\n<h3>I.N.S.P.I.R.E.</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Integrity</strong> - We say what we do and do what we say – we are accountable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Neighborliness</strong> - We build lasting relationships in and around our communities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Service</strong> - We deliver WESTclass service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Profitability</strong> - We reinvest our financial success in our communities and our team members.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Innovation</strong> - We are forward-thinking and committed to continuous improvement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Respect</strong> - We value diversity and encourage individual thinking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Excellence</strong> - We focus on the details and provide a WESTclass experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Our Mission</h2>\r\n<p>With absolute devotion, WESTliving delivers exceptional service and experiences by inspiring and empowering our team members to make a meaningful difference in the lives of those we serve.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Our Vision</h2>\r\n<p>WESTliving will be the most respected and recognized service company in the world.</p>', 'Maps & Directions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-04 17:13:22', '2014-09-04 17:13:22', '', 20, 'http://www.estanciads.com/redesign/20-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(248, 2, '2014-09-04 17:13:44', '2014-09-04 17:13:44', '<div class="media">\r\n  <div class="pull-left">\r\n    <img class="media-object" src="/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/John-Rimbach.jpg" alt="John Rimbach"/>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="media-body">\r\n    <h2 class="media-heading">John Rimbach</h2>\r\n    <h4>President</h4>\r\n    <p>Presented with a life fulfilling opportunity, John founded WESTliving in 2009. He provides the strategic direction for creating the unique experiences our residents enjoy and empowerment of our Team Members to professionally excel. His personal and professional experiences provide the guiding values our Company demonstrates in making a meaningful difference in the lives WESTliving touches. Always striving to do something special, his critical thinking, attention to detail and genuine interest for continuous improvement sets a standard that transcends the senior housing industry. His integrity and the guiding principles of his leadership resonate in his frequently articulating ‘Our collective success is through a true sense of belonging for all’ and ‘Surround yourself with those that are supportive of what you want to accomplish.’ With over two decades of industry knowledge in senior housing, including AF Evans Company, NCB Development Services, and Bank of America, he guides WESTliving with precision, passion and uncompromising leadership.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="media">\r\n  <div class="pull-left">\r\n    <img class="media-object" src="/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Patrick-Collins.jpg" alt="Patrick Collins"/>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="media-body">\r\n    <h2 class="media-heading">Patrick Collins</h2>\r\n    <h4>Vice President of Operations</h4>\r\n    <p>Patrick leads the operations team in WESTclass culture and focus. Through his many years in senior housing, his passion for creating a customer centered approach is the hallmark of his WESTliving leadership. Determined, yet genuine, you can see Patrick’s uncompromising leadership through careful selection of Team Members who model specific WESTclass service standards, bringing a unique environment to life in our communities. Prior to WESTliving, Patrick held leadership positions with SSL Consulting, Benchmark Assisted Living, Marriott International, and HCR/Manor Care. His experiences, both personal and professional, provide leadership with a focus and direction that a customer’s needs and desires are unique, guiding the call to action and promotion of WESTclass service.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="media">\r\n  <div class="pull-left">\r\n    <img class="media-object" src="/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/David-McBride.jpg" alt="David McBride"/>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="media-body">\r\n    <h2 class="media-heading">David McBride</h2>\r\n    <h4>Chief Technical Officer</h4>\r\n    <p>David leads the Information Technology department providing new services and equipment to meet the changing technological needs of the Company. He brings a progressive approach in IT solutions to streamline technologies and enhancing the WESTliving Team’s focus on the customer. David began his career in 1997 as a Help Desk Technician at West Corporation, one of the largest customer relationship management providers in the world. His success and progressive thinking earned him internal promotions through various positions, becoming the LAN Administration Manager for West Corporation in 2006. David joined the West Development Team, the Corporate Services division of WESTliving, in 2007 as the Information Technology Manager. With their expansive growth, and David’s innovative thinking and customer driven service approach, he earned a promotion to his currently held position as the Chief Technical Officer. The Information Technology department’s central interests remain in hospitality operations, healthcare technology, and care for seniors through education.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="media">\r\n  <div class="pull-left">\r\n    <img class="media-object" src="/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/Marc-Harper.jpg" alt="Marc Harper"/>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="media-body">\r\n    <h2 class="media-heading">Marc Harper</h2>\r\n    <h4>Chief Financial Officer</h4>\r\n    <p>Marc understands world class service at the home office is just as important for WESTclass service to be executed at the communities. He leads the administrative functions of accounting, Human Resources and Information Technology for WESTliving. His focus on client service, accountability and integrity has always served as guiding values in his professional life. Prior to joining WEST, Marc managed the Private Client Services practice of the Deloitte Tax LLP Orange County office as a Director. Marc was also previously Managing Director at myCFO, Inc. in Orange County, CA. He is a member of the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants, American Bar Association and California Society of CPAs and sits on several charitable boards throughout Orange and San Diego Counties.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="media">\r\n  <div class="pull-left">\r\n    <img style="width:140px;background-color:#eee;" class="media-object" src="/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/avatar_female.png" alt="Kimberly Holmes"/>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="media-body">\r\n    <h2 class="media-heading">Kimberly Holmes</h2>\r\n    <h4>Vice President of Financial Reporting and Analytics</h4>\r\n    <p>Providing financial tools that enable our Teams to proactively manage and provide more time to engage the customer is critical to Kimberly''s role. As a key contributor to guiding fiscal planning, Kimberly works with the communities to effectively map out fiscal performance objectives while developing strategic plans of appropriate financial stewardship. These tools enable a strong operating platform to deliver WESTclass services while strengthening our position to reinvest in our communities in many ways. With an extensive industry and service knowledge in both senior housing and hospitality, including SSL Consulting, Benchmark Assisted Living, Daley Hotel Group and Hotels of Distinction, Kimberly plays an extensive role in one of WESTliving''s core values; to reinvest our financial success in our communities and our Team Members.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="media">\r\n  <div class="pull-left">\r\n    <img style="width:140px;background-color:#eee;" class="media-object" src="/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/avatar_female.png" alt="Jessica Perez"/>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="media-body">\r\n    <h2 class="media-heading">Jessica Perez</h2>\r\n    <h4>Human Resources Director</h4>\r\n    <p>Jessica joined West Development, the Corporate Services division of WESTliving, in 2008 to provide Human Resources support to the Company''s premier hospitality entities. Her background in hospitality aligns perfectly with the WESTliving Team''s focus on service excellence. In her time with WESTliving, she has partnered with senior management on Team Member initiatives to champion WESTliving''s culture of exceptional service. Jessica has held Human Resources positions with Graphic Converting, Welk Resorts and Karl Strauss Breweries. Her focus on the internal customer, coupled with her drive to make a meaningful difference, add value to Team Member development, support and services.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>', 'Meet Our Team', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-04 17:13:44', '2014-09-04 17:13:44', '', 22, 'http://www.estanciads.com/redesign/22-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(249, 2, '2014-09-04 17:13:55', '2014-09-04 17:13:55', '<p class="intro-text">Gary and Mary West are successful entrepreneurs and pioneering philanthropists working together through their Foundation with a commitment to making a significant positive impact for the greater good. Their purposeful philanthropic investments include these initiative areas:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\r\n    <li>To significantly improve the lives of low-income seniors in San Diego and Omaha by supporting programs that address their needs.&nbsp; Enabling older adults to age independently and maintain health and wellness for as long as possible. In addition, the Foundation supports research efforts and validation processes through Infrastructure IndependentTM resources enabling seniors to better manage chronic disease and prevent unwanted hospitalizations.</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>To change the pattern of chronic unemployment in our urban neighborhoods by helping disadvantaged young people secure jobs with career advancement opportunity.</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>To support the training and deployment of service canines to people in need, especially seniors and disabled veterans of the Armed Forces of the United States.</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>To lower the cost of healthcare by encouraging innovative, patient-centered solutions by supporting medical and scientific research development, policy studies, education and advocacy.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Gary &amp; Mary pioneered West Corporation in 1986, a world recognized leader of technology-driven communications with more than 35,000 employees.&nbsp; West Corporation was sold to a consortium of private equity firms in 2006, enabling Gary &amp; Mary to pursue their purposeful philanthropic endeavors. Multiple business and non-profit entities resulted in the creation of: West Development, a hospitality operating company; <a href="http://www.garyandmarywestfoundation.org/" target="_blank">The Gary &amp; Mary West Foundation</a>, a philanthropic wireless health, caring for seniors and education entity; and West Partners, a private equity and real estate investment firm. WESTliving, a portfolio company of West Partners, was formed in 2009 to develop, acquire and manage senior housing communities, expanding Gary &amp; Mary’s long-term vision to support older adults.</p>', 'Events', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '24-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-04 17:13:55', '2014-09-04 17:13:55', '', 24, 'http://www.estanciads.com/redesign/24-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(250, 2, '2014-09-04 17:14:11', '2014-09-04 17:14:11', '<p class="intro-text">WESTliving''s hospitality focused approach to senior living is, in part, rooted in the business successes of Gary &amp; Mary West and their philosophy of gauging one''s success by what we are able to accomplish for our customers. Within WESTliving, serving our customers means continuing to foster ideas and expand our own capabilities to meet the growing and diverse needs of our customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Operating historically in an industry focused simply on trying to address the care needs of the elderly, WESTliving looks to shape senior housing and its own destiny by focusing on service excellence.&nbsp;Hiring, training, and mentoring service talented professionals, which brings our service culture to the benefit of others; leading to our success. WESTliving is among the first in its industry to adopt a set of Service Standards that parallel those of some of the best recognized services delivery companies in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today, we continue to bring added value to our own customer relationships and delivery platform, by bringing innovative ideas and improved possibilities to those we serve.&nbsp; We shamelessly take ideas and inspiration from other service-business leaders as well as other West businesses started by Gary and Mary that are more traditionally known for promoting hospitality and service quality.&nbsp; Our own restaurant and hotel businesses are operations with competencies and specialty areas that add to our base of knowledge and capabilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><a href="">West Inn &amp; Suites</a></strong>, an independent boutique hotel featuring 86 rooms with 36 suites opened its doors to in May of 2006. This pet-friendly hotel prides itself in superior guest service with value added amenities. Competing with brand properties in the local market makes unique services and amenities the hallmark for success. A complimentary breakfast buffet, free parking and Wi-Fi along with shuttle service within Carlsbad were the core value standards since opening. West Inn and Suites'' amenities include: Aveda products, a heated swimming pool (salt-water) and spa along with a business and fitness center. Our seasonal wine pour along with cookies and milk at bedtime make for a most enjoyable stay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The second restaurant, <strong><a href="">Bistro West<sup>®</sup></a></strong>, can be described as a chef driven bistro, serving contemporary comfort foods. It also features a diverse international wine list with an extensive selection of wines by the glass. Since it opened in May of 2007, the goal remains the same; we promise to provide our guests great food, wines and service in a beautiful restaurant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The first restaurant in Cannon Court was an exciting fine dining steak house, <strong><a href="">West Steak Seafood &amp; Spirits<sup>®</sup></a></strong>. The goal was to provide a fantastic dining experience by featuring only the finest foods, wine and service in a beautiful surrounding. This restaurant opened in December of 2005 to rave reviews and continues to build on its success. West Steak Seafood &amp; Spirits® specializes in prime steaks, but also has a large menu of appetizers, salads, seafood and homemade desserts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><a href="">Westmart<sup>®</sup></a></strong> was the first building in Cannon Court and opened for business in January of 2004. This premier gas station has 16 gasoline and 8 diesel fueling points along with a convenience store. Priding itself on competitive pricing, clean facilities, and excellent customer service, Westmart® adds to the amenities available at Cannon Court.</p>', 'Senior Resources', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '26-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-04 17:14:11', '2014-09-04 17:14:11', '', 26, 'http://www.estanciads.com/redesign/26-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(251, 2, '2014-09-04 17:14:28', '2014-09-04 17:14:28', '<h2>Acquisitions</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>WESTliving is looking to acquire existing senior living communities such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\r\n<li>Service enhanced (non-licensed) independent living communities</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Assisted living and memory care communities (licensed)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We are well capitalized and therefore not constrained by a financing or funding contingency in order to consummate a purchase.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With extensive experience in underwriting, marketing and operations of senior housing and a long-term investment viewpoint, WESTliving has the knowledge and flexibility to appropriately value your community. Unlike&nbsp;many investors in senior housing, WESTliving recognizes the importance of evaluating future income stream in emerging and stabilized markets to determine value rather than simply looking at the typical capitalization of in-place Net Operating Income. Our general acquisition criterion for&nbsp;existing operating communities is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\r\n    <li>Communities located in&nbsp;the Western-third of the United States</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>Market areas that comprise a middle or upper middle-income demographic</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>Communities that exceed 80 units with a complementary mix of studios, one-bedrooms and two-bedroom units</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>Communities that provide a range of services and programs catering to and addressing resident lifestyle, wellness and needs for changing care level</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>Communities less than 25 years old</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>Occupancy that is 70% or better</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Development</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>WESTliving is actively looking to secure quality&nbsp;sites for development throughout California. We prefer locations that have suburban or small town characteristics and a population or market area that exceeds 25,000 people.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The ideal development site for WESTliving is one that lies within the transition area separating&nbsp;downtown shopping and entertainment areas&nbsp;from primarily residential areas where the site has frontage along the roadway connecting these two areas. We consider the following when assessing land acquisition opportunities:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\r\n    <li>Three to seven acres of useable land area</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>Land area that can accommodate 80 to 150 units in a two- or possibly three-story design</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>Market areas that comprise a middle or upper middle-income demographic</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>Two points of access for ingress and egress</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>Located within a few miles of a hospital or major medical facility</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>Zoning and General Plan consistency that allows for senior housing development</li>\r\n    \r\n    <li>No required&nbsp;joint venture or partnership arrangement with a third party</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have an existing community you are considereing selling and would like to have WESTliving prepare a valuation anaylsis of your property or a land acquisition opportunity that may be suitable for WESTliving, please call (760) 602-5850 or email&nbsp;<a href="mailto:aandd@westliving.net">AandD@westliving.net</a>.</p>', 'Local Attractions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-04 17:14:28', '2014-09-04 17:14:28', '', 28, 'http://www.estanciads.com/redesign/28-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
