(776, 8, '2014-11-21 00:39:55', '2014-11-21 00:39:55', '<h3>Welcome to WESTclass service.</h3>\nYou''ve worked hard. Now it''s your turn to sit back and enjoy. Our signature WESTclass service ensures that you''re free from the small tasks that can so quickly eat up the day.\n\nFrom an attentive front desk to a personal concierge, we''re here to make sure that you don''t just hear the phrase "WESTclass service," you feel it.\n\nWhat will you do with a personal concierge, you ask? Of course we''re happy to book your next manicure, pedicure or massage, but we''ll also schedule your four-legged friend''s next dog walk. Want to try that "hot" new restaurant you''ve been hearing about? We''ll make the reservations. Need a gift for your visiting grandchild? We''ll do that and even get it wrapped. In need of a tropical getaway? We''ll handle the planning so that all you''ll have to do is pack your suitcase (which we''ll carry to the private car we''ve arranged to take you to the airport). Your concierge at <a href="http://www.mcdowellvillage.com/senior_living/living_options/independent_living.html">independent living in Scottsdale</a> will become so indispensable; you''ll wonder what you did without one until now.\n\nYes, WESTclass service means your happiness is our happiness, so we''re looking forward to getting to know your smile. From scheduled transportation to dry cleaning to opera tickets, isn''t it nice to know we''ve thought of everything?', 'Concierge', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '272-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-11-21 00:39:55', '2014-11-21 00:39:55', '', 272, 'http://dev.mcdowellvillage.com/blog/272-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(777, 8, '2014-11-21 00:39:57', '2014-11-21 00:39:57', '<h3>Welcome to WESTclass service.</h3>\r\nYou''ve worked hard. Now it''s your turn to sit back and enjoy. Our signature WESTclass service ensures that you''re free from the small tasks that can so quickly eat up the day.\r\n\r\nFrom an attentive front desk to a personal concierge, we''re here to make sure that you don''t just hear the phrase "WESTclass service," you feel it.\r\n\r\nWhat will you do with a personal concierge, you ask? Of course we''re happy to book your next manicure, pedicure or massage, but we''ll also schedule your four-legged friend''s next dog walk. Want to try that "hot" new restaurant you''ve been hearing about? We''ll make the reservations. Need a gift for your visiting grandchild? We''ll do that and even get it wrapped. In need of a tropical getaway? We''ll handle the planning so that all you''ll have to do is pack your suitcase (which we''ll carry to the private car we''ve arranged to take you to the airport). Your concierge at <a href="http://www.mcdowellvillage.com/senior_living/living_options/independent_living.html">independent living in Scottsdale</a> will become so indispensable; you''ll wonder what you did without one until now.\r\n\r\nYes, WESTclass service means your happiness is our happiness, so we''re looking forward to getting to know your smile. From scheduled transportation to dry cleaning to opera tickets, isn''t it nice to know we''ve thought of everything?', 'Concierge', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '272-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-21 00:39:57', '2014-11-21 00:39:57', '', 272, 'http://dev.mcdowellvillage.com/blog/272-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(778, 8, '2014-11-21 00:49:21', '2014-11-21 00:49:21', '<h3>Variety is the spice of breakfast, lunch and dinner - McDowell Village Style</h3>\nWhat could be better than sitting down to a delicious meal made with wholesome ingredients? A menu full of tasty choices of course. Here at McDowell Village, our chefs prepare a variety of entrees at every meal. So you can get what you''re craving every time. Have a favorite personal recipe? Share it with our staff and we''ll do our best to ensure that it''s offered on the menu.\n\nOf course, dining options aren''t confined to the menu. Feel free to meet friends in our main restaurant or choose to dine "al fresco" poolside. Or join us in the Scottsdale sunshine for an afternoon barbecue or sunset supper.\n\n<a href="http://www.mcdowellvillage.com/senior_living/menus/index.html">Visit our Menu page to learn more about our delicious cuisine.</a>', 'Restaurant Dining or Casual Bistro', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '274-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-11-21 00:49:21', '2014-11-21 00:49:21', '', 274, 'http://dev.mcdowellvillage.com/blog/274-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(798, 8, '2014-11-25 23:42:27', '2014-11-25 23:42:27', '<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Debbie-Whipple.png" alt="Debbie Whipple" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Debbie Whipple</h2>\r\n<h4>General Manager</h4>\r\nDebbie holds the General Manager position at McDowell Village. She began her career at McDowell Village in the sales and marketing department when the community opened in January of 2006. In 2007 she was promoted to General Manager. Debbie left McDowell Village briefly in 2011 to pursue another opportunity within the market. We were fortunate to welcome her back to our community in October of 2012.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining McDowell Village Debbie worked in the marketing and finance fields. She is married, has one daughter, and is very involved in her community. She currently holds the position of President of Freedom Academy School Board of Directors. Debbie has an undergraduate degree in Broadcasting from the University of Oklahoma.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Michael-Bergmans.png" alt="Michael Bergmans" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Michael Bergmans</h2>\r\n<h4>Assistant General Manager</h4>\r\nMichael started his career as a chef and spent over 18 years in some of Arizona''s top restaurants and catering companies. He toured the country as a private chef for some celebrities including; Bette Midler, Ricky Martin, Tina Turner, NSYNC, Cher and Janet Jackson. Michael has taken his love for people and commitment to customer service to the next level as Assistant General Manager. For the past 3 years Michael has enjoyed working with management and the residents to make McDowell Village one of the top Senior Residents in the area. He has used his experience in the food industry to keep the McDowell Village Restaurant fresh and inviting.\r\n\r\n"I am thrilled to be a part of the team at McDowell Village and I am excited to extend an invite to come and dine in our restaurant. While you''re here, take a tour of the entire resort-like community! You will soon discover the McDowell Village is where you belong."\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Chef-Thomas-Miranda.png" alt="Thomas Miranda" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Thomas Miranda</h2>\r\n<h4>Chef</h4>\r\nThomas has been in the food and beverage industry for 13 years, he has a real passion for food and loves to cook. His prior restaurant position before joining the team at McDowell Village was at a similar senior living community in North Phoenix. "My favorite meal to cook is BBQ Ribs, baked beans and cream corn…mmm”. I am proud to be the Executive Chef of McDowell Village and hope to take food and service to another level. My hobbies include playing basketball and spending time with my son Josh."\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Jay-Beaird.png" alt="Jay Beaird" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Jay Beaird</h2>\r\n<h4>Marketing Director</h4>\r\nJay has been with McDowell Village since August 2008. Prior to joining McDowell Village Jay had a very successful career in the toy and hobby industry. He was a manufactures representative for over 30 companies and his previous position before joining McDowell was as the Western Regional Sales Manager for the world’s largest model railroad company. Jay is married with six children and two grandchildren.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Kristin-Koga-London.png" alt="Kristin Koga-London" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Kristin Koga-London</h2>\r\n<h4>Marketing Manager</h4>\r\nKristin has been with McDowell Village since June 2010. Prior to joining McDowell Village Kristin was a regional sales director and has had a long, successful sales and marketing career. Kristin has a dual degree in Business Management and Marketing. She is married and is the mother of two boys.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Pam-Clark.png" alt="Pam Clark" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Pam Clark</h2>\r\n<h4>Business Office Manager</h4>\r\nPam has worked at McDowell Village since 2006 and was the Front Desk Supervisor before becoming the Business Office Manager. She was born and raised in North Dakota and has lived in Arizona since 1983. Pam acquired her customer service and bookkeeping skills while helping her husband run a small business for over 20 years. They have two daughters. "This job is never boring. There is always something interesting happening."\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Chris-Okeke.png" alt="Chris Okeke" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Chris Okeke</h2>\r\n<h4>Fitness Instructor</h4>\r\nChris is the Fitness Instructor at McDowell Village. He has a passion for working with seniors, having grown up spending a lot of time with his own grandparents. He gained experience working in outpatient/inpatient physical therapy clinics. Chris earned his Bachelor of Science degree in Exercise &amp; Fitness Management from the University of Central Oklahoma. He is married and has two dogs.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Teri-Azlin.png" alt="Teri Azlin" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Teri Azlin</h2>\r\n<h4>Activities Director</h4>\r\nTeri has been with McDowell Village since May of 2008. Although her current position is a new field for her, she has been in the "people" business her entire career. Teri''s degree is in the field of Architecture, an industry she worked in for several years. After having children Teri switched careers to work as an administrative assistant and helped run an office with 100+ employees, which gave her a flexible schedule before moving to McDowell Village. She is married and has two children.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img class="margin-top-10" src="/wp-content/uploads/Ilona-Herbelin.png" alt="Ilona Herbelin" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-9">\r\n<h2>Ilona Herbelin</h2>\r\n<h4>Resident Services Director</h4>\r\nIlona is the Resident Service Director for Assisted Living at McDowell. She was present for the foundation and development of the Assisted Living services in 2010. She is a Registered Nurse with a background in cardiology, acute care, geriatrics and business management. Ilona is passionate about her work and advocacy for our residents.\r\n\r\nIlona is married and has two small children. She is an avid animal lover, and dog owner. Ilona is originally from Oregon and returns to visit the coast any chance she can get. During her time off she enjoys photography, travel, antiquing, real estate, off-roading and swimming with her children.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Meet Our Team', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-25 23:42:27', '2014-11-25 23:42:27', '', 22, 'http://dev.mcdowellvillage.com/blog/22-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
